olkata or enjoy free time.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;color:black"=""><o:p><font size="3" face="arial">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="arial"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Day 01: Kolkata &gt;&gt; Bagdogra/ NJP &gt;&gt;\r\nDarjeeling</span></b><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="arial"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><br></span></b></font></p>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">Pick up from Bagdogra Airport and drop to\r\n     Queen of the hill stations,&nbsp; named derived from “ Dorje-Line” which\r\n     means the place of “Dorje”, the mystic thunderbolt. Covering a distance of\r\n     88 km over a drive of 3.5 hrs along winding roads, it is an experience of\r\n     unforgettable beauty.<o:p></o:p></font></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">Checked-in at Hotel &gt; short tour in evening\r\n     for window shopping &gt; overnight stay.</font></span></li></ul><font size="3" face="arial"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><div><font size="3" face="arial"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><br></span></b></font></div>Day 02: Darjeeling</span></b></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="3"><b><br></b></font><ul type="disc"><li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">Start the day at 4am with an early morning\r\n     trip to Tiger Hill (780 ft) to catch the sunrise behind the majestic\r\n     Kunchenjunga range.<o:p></o:p></font></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">On the way back visit the Ghoom Monastery\r\n     &amp; Batasia Loop.<o:p></o:p></font></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">Back to the hotel for breakfast &gt; proceed\r\n     for half day sightseeing of the Himalayan Mountaineering Institute,\r\n     Ropeway, Zoo, Tenzing Rock, Japanese Temple, Tea Garden &amp; Tibetan\r\n     Refugees Self Help Centre.<o:p></o:p></font></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">Back to the hotel by evening &gt; Take a walk\r\n     to “Chowrasta” the center point fo the Mall area for window shopping &gt;\r\n     Overnight stay.</font></span></li></ul>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="arial"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><br></span></b></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="arial"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Day 03: Darjeeling</span></b><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="arial"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><br></span></b></font></p>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">After breakfast take a trip to “Mirik (6000\r\n     ft)- the newest hill-station in Dajeeling hills famous for its squash (the\r\n     vegetable) &amp; the picturesque lake, the quiet township is also\r\n     surrounded by gardens which produces some the finest teas. The lake offers\r\n     boating and fishing apart from a view of snowcapped peaks. Enjoy the fulfilling\r\n     experience of nature in its purest form mingled with the unique culture\r\n     prevalent there. Spend the rest of the day at Mirik to reach Darjeeling\r\n     back by sunset.<o:p></o:p></font></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">Go back to hotel for overnight stay.</font></span></li></ul>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="3" face="arial"><br></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="3" face="arial">Day 04: Darjeeling &gt; Bagdogra/NJP &gt; Kolkata&nbsp;</font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="3" face="arial"><br></font></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial"=""><font size="3" face="arial">Depart to Bagdogra/ NJP after breakfast.</font><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; font-size: 10pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<!--EndFragment--></div><br>', 'Round trip (Dhaka-Kolkata-Dhaka) , Round trip (Kolkata-Bagdogra-Kolkata) by Jet Airways India, Meals as\r\nper plan shown above in RED, all taxes,All transfers &amp; sightseeing by 01\r\nNAC Wagon R/NAC Sumo Ex Bagdogra Airport/NJP Station which is not on disposal\r\nbut point-to-point,Gangtok Local Sightseeing would be by 01 NAC Wagon R (02\r\nPax), 02 Wagon R (04 Pax &amp; above)', 'Entrance/Guide/camera fees etc,4.50% GST on\r\nbilling amount,Visit to Nathula Pass @ Rs. 4500/- extra on the total cost by\r\nper vehicle,En-route visit to Chardham (Namchi) @ Rs. 1700/- per vehicle extra\r\non the total cost,Joy ride on the toy train in Darjeeling @ Rs. 550/- per person\r\n+ Rs. 600 per Vehicle cost,Any difference arising due to increase in fuel price\r\nor change in taxes levied by the government, Difference in cost arising due to\r\nmishaps, bandhs/strikes, natural calamities like landslides, road blockages\r\netc,&nbsp; In such a case, the extra cost would have to be paid on the spot by\r\nthe guest directly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '2017-01-01', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'Darjeeling_4.jpg-1490084213.jpg', 'Darjeeling_2.jpg-1490084213.jpg,Darjeeling_6.jpg-1490084213.jpg,Darjeeling_5.jpg-1490084213.jpg', 3, 39999, '2017-03-21 15:16:53', '2017-04-05 18:11:47');
