free time.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;">Day 01: Kolkata-Cochin</span></span><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">Meet &amp; assist after arrival Cochin International Airport &gt; transfer to hotels<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">After lunch go for sightseeing at historical fort Cochin which has a rich heritage and strong historical &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;relationship with English, Portuguese, Dutch, Arabs, Chinese etc.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">You can visit Dutch palace, Asia’s best preserved Synagogue, Chinese fish nets, sea mouth, Beach walkway &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; etc. &gt; Overnight stay.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><font size="4"><br></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;">Day 02: Cochin Munnar (140 km approx. /4 hrs)</span></span><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">After breakfast drive to Munnar hills (130 kms), the green paradise of Kerala with unending expands of tea plantations, spice plantations and a variety of flora and fauna.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">Check in your hill resort and after noon we’ll visit Munnar town and nearby places.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">Go back to hotel for overnight stay.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><font size="4"><br></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;">Day 03: Munnar</span></span><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">Starts with breakfast &gt; go for sightseeing at Muttupetty Dam, a beautiful spot for viewing the picturesque Munnar, Kundala Lake- a natural lake with recreational facilities like boating and having excellent view of western ghats as well as the surrounded by forest Besides visit eco point and tea plantations.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">After noon you can visit Eravikulam National park; where the endangering Nilgiri Tahr is preserved. Later drive back to your resort for overnight stay.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><font size="4"><br></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;">Day 04: Munnar Thekkady (100 km approx.)</span></span><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">After breakfast drive toward thekkady ,wildlife destination of Kerala also known as the spice bag of the state. You can enjoy a beautiful journey through the hills and valleys of Western Ghat to reach this jungle destination.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">Check in your hotel and later go for an optional Kathakali show, Spice plantation visit, elephant ride or an&nbsp;Ayurvedic massage treatment there.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">You’ll also have amazing boat ride in Periyar Lake which flows through the Periyar Tiger reserve and that will give you chance to watch the wild animals like elephant, Bison, Sambar, Deer etc are roaming the both shore.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">Go back to hotel for overnight stay.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><font size="4"><br></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 21.15pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;">Day 05: Thekkady to Allepey (Houseboat)</span></span><span style="font-family: ABeeZee; color: black;"><o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">After breakfast check out your resort and drive to Alleppey which is known as Venice of the east for its special geographical features as the place is famous for its vast back water stretches and paddy fields.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">By noon you can board your houseboat to explore the backwaters and its serene beauty and enjoy the ride, delicious cuisines and overnight stay onboard.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial;color:black;background:white"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;"><font size="4"><br></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span times="" new="" roman";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial;color:black;background:white"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;"><font size="4">Day 06: Alleppey – Cochin ( 60 Km approx 01 hours)</font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;"><font size="4"><o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span times="" new="" roman";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="" style="font-family: ABeeZee;">After breakfast drive to Cochin &gt; Check in Hotel<o:p></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; text-indent: -18pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><font size="4"><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: black;">·<span times="" new="" roman""="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;