(82, 1, 0, 0, 'BEST OF HANOI', 'VIETNAM', 'HANOI', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '4 Days / 3 Nights', NULL, '<div style="text-align: justify;"><font size="3"><span style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Planning for a tour in Hanoi? Need a tour plan for exploring this amazing city? Want to see all of the highlights of this city? Never fear, join this Hanoi tour which covers the historic hot spots, must-see monument, and special spaces that you''d kick yourself for missing.</span><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial;">Hanoi, the capital of Vietnam, is known for its centuries-old architecture and a rich culture with Southeast Asian, Chinese and French influences. At its heart is the chaotic Old Quarter, where the narrow streets are roughly arranged by trade. There are many little temples, including Bach Ma, honoring a legendary horse, plus Đồng Xuân Market, selling household goods and street food. (Source: Wikipedia)&nbsp;</span></font></div>', '<div><font face="arial" size="3"><div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"=""><font face="arial" size="3"><div style="text-align: justify; font-weight: bold;">Day 01: Hanoi arrival (D)</div><div style="text-align: justify; font-weight: bold;"><br></div><div style="text-align: justify;">1. Arrive in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam</div><div style="text-align: justify;">2. Pick up from International airport and transfer to the hotel. (check in after 14:00)</div><div style="text-align: justify;">3. Leisure hours to roam around the city.</div><div style="text-align: justify;">4. Dinner at local restaurant.</div><div style="text-align: justify; font-weight: bold;"><br></div></font></div><div style="text-align: justify; font-weight: bold;" helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"=""><font face="arial" size="3"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Day 02: Hanoi – Halong (B/L/D)</span><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify; font-weight: bold;" helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"=""><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Full day City Tour: Ba Dinh Square, Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum (close on Monday, Friday and from September – October for renovate) House on Still, One Pillar Pagoda, Temple of Literature- the first university of Vietnam</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Lunch at local restaurant before transfer to Halong City.&nbsp;</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">Notes:</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">&nbsp;a. Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum is closed on Mondays, Fridays, all afternoons and also closed on Sep– Oct every year for renovation activities</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">&nbsp;b. Vietnam Ethnology is closed on all Mondays and during Vietnamese Traditional Lunar New Year</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">If travel date falls on any of these days, we will switch it to the next day or find alternative options.</font></div><div style="text-align: justify; font-weight: bold;" helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"=""><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify; font-weight: bold;" helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"=""><font face="arial" size="3"><span style="font-weight: 700;">Day 03: Halong – Hanoi (B/L/D)</span></font></div><div style="text-align: justify; font-weight: bold;" helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"=""><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Breakfast</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Tuan Chau Island for boarding on day cruise, 4 hours sight seeing the Halong Bay.&nbsp;</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">3. Visit Thien Cung Grotto Cave- one of famous caves in Ha Long&nbsp;</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">4. Lunch is served on boat while cruising back to habour.</font></div><div helvetica="" neue",="" helvetica,="" arial,="" sans-serif;="" font-size:="" 14px;="" font-weight:="" normal;"="" style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">5. Transfer back to Hanoi, at arrival take a walking tour to visit Hoan Kiem Lake, Ngoc Son Temple and shopping at the Old Quarter.</font></di