(83, 1, 0, 0, 'HO CHI MINH HIGHLIGHTS, VIETNAM !', 'VIETNAM', 'HO CHI MINH', 'TSL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '4 Days / 3 Nights', NULL, '<div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">Ho Chi Minh City is the southern part of Vietnam, famous for the pivotal role it played in the Vietnam War. It''s also known for its French colonial landmarks, including Notre-Dame Cathedral, made entirely of materials imported from France, and the 19th-century Central Post Office. Food stalls line the city’s streets, especially around bustling Bến Thành Market.</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium;">The story of wartime Saigon is told at the War Remnants Museum, the tunnel network at Củ Chi and Independence Palace, where North Vietnamese tanks famously breached the gates in April 1975. The Saigon Zoo and Botanical Gardens are home to elephants, tigers and rare orchids. Native plants and animals may also be seen at the Cần Giờ Biosphere Reserve, a mangrove forest at the mouth of the Saigon River. The Jade Emperor Pagoda is filled with incense and carved figurines, and features elaborate statuary and a turtle pond.(Source: Wikipedia)</span><br></div>', '<div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><b>Day 1: Ho Chi Minh arrival (D)</b></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Arrive in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Pick up from International airport to the hotel. (check in after 14:00)</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">3. Leisure hours to travel around hotel.</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">4. Dinner at local restaurant. &nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><b>Day 2: Cu Chi Tunnels – Ho Chi Minh City tour (B/L/D)</b></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Breakfast at Hotel</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Chu Chu Tunnel visit&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">3. Reunification Palace visit at after noon.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">4. Cathedral stands visit, the Saigon Post Office</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">5. Finally visit Ben Thanh Market</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">6. Overnight in Ho Chi Minh City hotel</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><b>Day 3: Ho Chi Minh City tour &nbsp;- Mekong Delta (My Tho) (B/L/D)</b></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Breakfast at hotel</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Travel from Ho Chi Minh City to the area referred to locally as ‘the rice bowl of Vietnam”.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">3. Upon arrival My Tho, board in a cruise among the aptly named Dragon, Unicorn, Turtle and Phoenix Islands.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">4. Activities of the day : a horse cart ride along country roads, an adventurous rowing boat through the Xep Canal amongst a forest of palm trees.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">5. Return to Ho Chi Minh City in the late afternoon.</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">6. Dinner and overnight in Ho Chi Minh City.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><b>Day 4: Ho Chi Minh City Departure (B)</b></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Breakfast at hotel</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Check out (befofe 12:00)</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">3. Drop to Airport</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><br></div></div>', 'Airfares (international),03 nights’ shared Accommodation in twin/double room with daily breakfast at the below indicated room types (see hotel category list below) (check in and check out around noontime),All transfers and transportation with air-con vehicles (types of vehicles depending on the number of pax),Local ENGLISH speaking guides,All entrance fees as program,Private boat in Mekong Delta,Meals (B/L/D) (Breakfast/Lunch/Dinner) as indicated in the program (Halah food in Ho Chi Minh City – local food in My Tho),02 bottles of mineral water per person per day on bus on days of transfer and sightseeing only', 'Meals (other than mentioned in the program),Drinks,Visas to Vietnam,Mineral water beyond that supplied,Tips,Early check in or late check out,Insurances,Optional excursions and activities,Additional transfer required due to any emergency situation,Items of a personal nature (Phone calls, laundry, beverages…),Peak season surcharges if any,All not mentioned above', 'The above tour prices are based on our current transportation rates. Increasing petrol rates might affect our transportation and boat fees, in which case we reserve the right to revise our current rates. If any increase should arise we will of course keep you well informed.,Availability:Please note that if a certain hotel is not available at the time of booking, then we will gladly make alternative suggestions in the same category. We will advise you accordingly with the surcharge if any. As a result we would highly appreciate it if you could advise us to block rooms soonest possible to guarantee the rooms and rates in period of high and peak season,All the above points of interest are open for visit based on current updates. In case of closure for construction or any other reason, we will replace with a similar point of interest,Above itinerary is based on the current flight schedule. In case of flight changes, the itinerary will be changed accordingly.&nbsp;No early check in or late checkout is included except those indicated in the program. Generally, the check in time is 14.00pm and check out time is 12.00pm,&nbsp;Visas into Vietnam is required except for countries who have signed the visa exemption contracts. Please contact us for visa information details,&nbsp;', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '2017-01-01', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'Vietnam-Campuchia-Ho-Chi-Minh-City.jpg-1490152864.jpg', 'Untitled.jpg-1490101307.jpg,BEN_THANH_MARKET_SAIGON_HO_CHI_MINH_CITY_VIETNAM_JAN_2012_(6940808167).jpg-1490101307.jpg,Untitled-1.jpg-1490101307.jpg', 4, 51000, '2017-03-21 17:24:56', '2017-03-29 13:52:39'),
(84, 1, 0, 0, 'HELLO HANOI', 'VIETNAM', 'HANOI', 'TSL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '3 Days / 2 Nights', NULL, '<div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Planning for a tour in Hanoi? Need a tour plan for exploring this amazing city? Want to see all of the highlights of this city? Never fear, join this Hanoi tour which covers the historic hot spots, must-see monument, and special spaces that you''d kick yourself for missing.</span><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial; font-size: medium;">Hanoi, the capital of Vietnam, is known for its centuries-old architecture and a rich culture with Southeast Asian, Chinese and French influences. At its heart is the chaotic Old Quarter, where the narrow streets are roughly arranged by trade. There are many little temples, including Bach Ma, honoring a legendary horse, plus Đồng Xuân Market, selling household goods and street food.(Source: Wikipedia)</span></div>', '<div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><b>Day 01: Hanoi arrival (D)</b></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Pick up from Airport and drive to Hanoi Hotel. ( Check in time 14.00)</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Leisure time to travel around the city.</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">3. Dinner at hotel</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><b>Day 02: Hanoi City tour (B/L/D)</b></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Full day City Tour: Ba Dinh Square, Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum (close on Monday, Friday and from September – October for renovate) House on Still, One Pillar Pagoda, Temple of Literature- the first university of Vietnam,Ethnology Museum (closed on Monday- replace by Fine Art Museum),Hoan Kiem Lake, Ngoc Son Temple and shopping at the Old Quarter.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Lunch at Local Restaurent.</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">3. Dinner at hotel</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">Notes:</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">&nbsp;a. Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum is closed on Mondays, Fridays, all afternoons, closed on Sep– Oct every year for renovation activities</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">&nbsp;b. Vietnam Ethnology is closed on all Mondays and during Vietnamese Traditional Lunar New Year</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">&nbsp;If travel date falls on any of these days, we will switch it to the next day or find alternative options.</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><b>Day 03: Hanoi departure (B)</b></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">1. Depend on flight time, free time until check out (before 12:00)&nbsp;</font></div><div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" size="3">2. Drop at &nbsp;airport.&nbsp;</font></div><div><br></div>', 'Airfares (international),03 nights shared Accommodation in twin/double room with daily breakfast at the below indicated room types (see hotel category list below) (check in and check out around noontime),All transfers and transportation with air-con vehicles (types of vehicles depending on the numb