(89, 1, 0, 0, 'WITNESS PARADISE SRI LANKA !!', 'SRI LANKA', 'KANDY - BENTOTA', 'TSL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '4 Days / 3 Nights', NULL, '<div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: medium;">Sri Lanka is filled with romantic landscapes, governed by rising mountains, lush forests, ocean like tanks and gushing waterfalls, that it was considered the lost paradise by many a globe trotters, who fell upon the country. The golden beaches of the country had been praised for their picture postcard view </span><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="font-size: medium; white-space: pre;"></span><span style="font-size: medium;">since eternity. The central highlands of the island are filled with pictures of stirring mountains carpeted with lush green tea gardens, roaring waterfalls mingling with the clouds and landscapes shimmering in sunlight and disappearing under the rising mist. North of Sri Lanka is a world apart from the rest of country. Colourful Hindu temples replace the white pagodas while sari clad damsels roam the streets on bicycles. On the western coasts of the country is Colombo, a capital city of the island, which displays a rich colonial heritage. A potpourri of races, religions and cultures, Colombo parades the best and worst the country has to offer.&nbsp;</span></div>', '<div><b><font size="3">DAY 01: AIRPORT–PINNAWELA - KANDY&nbsp;</font></b></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3">Meet and assist at the BIA Airport.</font></div><div><font size="3">Proceed to Kandy (Approximately 04 hours Airport-Kandy.</font></div><div><font size="3">Visit Pinnawala Elephant Orphanage - It was established in 1975 by the Sri Lanka Wildlife Department in a 25 acre coconut property adjoining the Maha Oya River. Pinnawala has now become one of the bigger orphanages and is quite well known worldwide. Animals are allowed to roam freely during the day and a herd structure allowed form.( Entrance fee – USD 35 per/USD 23 per child ).</font></div><div><font size="3">The city of Kandy, which lies in the centre of Sri Lanka at an elevation of about 485 meters above sea level.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="3">The Ulpange or the Queen’s bathing Pavilion - Situated partly in the waters of the Kandy Lake and the other part on land near the Temple of the Tooth Relic.</font></div><div><font size="3">Kandy Lake - This artificial lake was built by the last king of Kandy .</font></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3">Visit the Kandy Museum and the Market Place.</font></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3">Hotel &nbsp;: Ozo Kandy.</font></div><div><font size="3">Meals &nbsp;: Bed and Breakfast basis.</font></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><b><font size="3">DAY 02: KANDY – BENTOTA</font></b></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3">After breakfast proceed to Waskaduwa (Approximately 04 hours).</font></div><div><font size="3">Madu River - The bio-diversity of the Madu River is of monumental signification when considering the wide ranges of aquatic and avian life as well as wetland dwelling amphibians, reptiles, mammals that inhabit the environs of this natural treasure. Bird watchers will be pleased to know that 111 species of bird have been identified in the mangrove formed environs of the river, and has been known to host several types of migratory birds.</font></div><div><font size="3">Take a boat ride at the river ( Per Boat – TK. 2200).</font></div><div><font size="3">Kosgoda Sea Turtle - Conservation Project operated by the Wild Life Protection Society of Sri Lanka, It was established in 1988 to protect Sri Lanka’s turtles from extinction (Per adult/child – TK. 900).</font></div><div><font size="3">Hotel &nbsp;: Taprobana Wadduwa.</font></div><div><font size="3">Meals &nbsp;: Bed and Breakfast.</font></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><b><font size="3">DAY 03: BENTOTA</font></b></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3">Breakfast at the hotel.</font></div><div><font size="3">At leisure.</font></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3">Hotel &nbsp;: Taprobana Wadduwa.</font></div><div><font size="3">Meals &nbsp;: Bed and Breakfast.</font></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><b><font size="3">DAY 04: WADDUWA - AIRPORT&nbsp;</font></b></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3">After breakfast relax at the hotel.</font></div><div><font size="3">Later proceed to airport for departure flight (Approximately 02 hours) - Please be at the airport 05 hours prior to flight departure.</font></div><div><br></div>', 'All Highway Toll fees,Hotel Accommodation at the above mentioned hotels on 01 DBL Room – BB basis,&nbsp;Hotels check in by 12:00 hrs. Check out by at 12:00 noon unless otherwise arranged,Hotels will be confirmed on availability at the time of booking. Alternatives will be suggested (if unavailable) prior to confirmation,', 'Airfare and Visa fee.(Online Visa application can be done at www.eta.gov.lk),Cost of Lunch &amp; Dinner throughout the tour,Expenses of personal nature,Any other service not specified above.Entrance fees &amp; joining fees for adventure tours and safari tours,Sightseeing places not included in the Tour Agenda,Meal costs other than included in the Hotel bookings,Driver tips,Transport -A/C CAR – USD 65 Per day', '', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '2017-03-21', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'kandy-buddha_2652049a-large.jpg-1490175481.jpg', 'sea-turtles-Kosgoda-640x400.jpg-1490176431.jpg,,', 4, 61500, '2017-03-22 16:38:01', '2017-03-29 13:19:34'),
