(92, 1, 0, 0, 'FOUR DAYS IN AMAZING SRILANKA', 'SRI LANKA', 'KANDY - NUWARA ELIYA - COLOMBO', 'TSL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '4 Days / 3 Nights', NULL, '<div>Sri Lanka is filled with romantic landscapes, governed by rising mountains, lush forests, ocean like tanks and gushing waterfalls, that it was considered the lost paradise by many a globe trotters, who fell upon the country. The golden beaches of the country had been praised for their picture postcard views since eternity. The central highlands of the island are filled with pictures of stirring mountains carpeted with lush green tea gardens, roaring waterfalls mingling with the clouds and landscapes shimmering in sunlight and disappearing under the rising mist. North of Sri Lanka is a world apart from the rest of country. Colorful Hindu temples replace the white pagodas while sari clad damsels roam the streets on bicycles. On the western coasts of the country is Colombo, a capital city of the island, which displays a rich colonial heritage. A potpourri of races, religions and cultures, Colombo parades the best and worst the country has to offer.&nbsp;<br></div><div>&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>', '<div><span style="font-size: medium;"><b>DAY 01: AIRPORT–PINNAWELA - KANDY&nbsp;</b></span><br></div><div><font size="3">Meet and assist at the BIA Airport.</font></div><div><font size="3">Proceed to Kandy (Approximately 04 hours Airport-Kandy.</font></div><div><font size="3">Visit Pinnawala Elephant Orphanage - It was established in 1975 by the Sri Lanka Wildlife Department in a 25 acre coconut property adjoining the Maha Oya River. Pinnawala has now become one of the bigger orphanages and is quite well known worldwide. Animals are allowed to roam freely during the day and a herd structure allowed form. ( Entrance fee – TK. 3000 per adult &amp; 2000 &nbsp;per child).</font></div><div><font size="3">The city of Kandy, which lies in the centre of Sri Lanka at an elevation of about 485 meters above sea level.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="3">The Ulpange or the Queen’s bathing Pavilion - Situated partly in the waters of the Kandy Lake and the other part on land near the Temple of the Tooth Relic.</font></div><div><font size="3">Kandy Lake - This artificial lake was built by the last king of Kandy.</font></div><div><font size="3">Visit the Kandy Museum and the Market Place.</font></div><div><font size="3">&nbsp;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span></font></div><div><font size="3"><b>DAY 02: KANDY&nbsp;</b></font></div><div><font size="3">After breakfast relax at the hotel&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="3">Visit The Royal Botanical Garden, Peradeniya which is situated about 5 km to the west of the city center at Peradeniya. It is visited by 2 million people per year(Entrance fee –TK. 1500 Per adult / child)</font></div><div><font size="3">Evening, leisure on your own.</font></div><div><font size="3"><b><br></b></font></div><div><font size="3"><b>DAY 03: KANDY - NUWARA ELIYA&nbsp;</b></font></div><div><font size="3">After breakfast proceed to Nuwara Eliya (Approximately 03 hours).&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="3">Nuwara Eliya - Located in the heart of Sri Lankan hill country. Nuwara Eliya, also known as ‘Little’ England’, was the favorite hill station of the British who tried to create the resort into a typical English Village.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="3">Visit to a Tea Factory - where you will witness how the world famous Ceylon Tea is produced and enjoy a cup of Ceylon Tea while enjoying the spectacular scenery.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span></font></div><div><font size="3">Ramboda Falls - Witness the Ramboda Water Fall&amp; en-route you can stop and take a sightseeing tour including a visit to a Tea Factory where you will witness how the world famous Ceylon Tea is produced and enjoy a cup of Ceylon Tea while enjoying the spectacular scenery.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3"><b>DAY 04: NUWARA ELIYA </b>&nbsp;</font></div><div><font size="3">After breakfast relax at the hotel.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span></font></div><div><font size="3">Afternoon, visit the Gregory’s Lake. Gregory Lake was build under the period of British Governor Sir William Gregory in 1873. This is the most prominent attraction in Nuwara Eliya (Entrance fee – TK. 800 Per adult/child )</font></div><div><font size="3">&nbsp;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span></font></div><div><font size="3"><br></font></div><div><font size="3"><b>DAY 05: NUWARA ELIYA – COLOMBO&nbsp;</b></font></div><div><font size="3">After breakfast proceed to Colombo (Approximately 06 hours)-Colombo city is full of popular tourist attractions.</font></div><div><font size="3">National Museum - The National Museum of Colombo was established in 1877 by the British Governor Sir William Gregory which is the largest Museum in Sri Lanka. It has a good collection of historical work.</font></div><div><font size="3">Galle Face Green - South of Colombo along with the lined palm trees of Galle road is the Galle face Green. Along with the a greenish seafront you can enjoy the evening breeze and view the sun set.</font></div><div><font size="3">Hotel: Steuart Hotel Colombo</font></div><div><font size="3">Meals: &nbsp;Bed and Breakfast</font></div><div><font size="3"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></font></div><div><font size="3"><b>DAY 06: COLOMBO - AIRPORT&nbsp;</b></font></div><div><font size="3">After breakfast relax at the hotel</font></div><div><font size="3">Later proceed to airport for departure flight (Approximately 01 hour) - Please be at the airport 05 hours prior to flight departure.</font></div><div><br></div>', 'All Highway Toll fees,Hotel Accommodation at the above mentioned hotels on 01 DBL Room – BB basis,&nbsp;Hotels check in by 12:00 hrs. Check out by at 12:00 noon unless otherwise arranged,Hotels will be confirmed on availability at the time of booking. Alternatives will be suggested (if unavailable) prior to confirmation,', 'Airfare and Visa fee.(Online Visa application can be done at www.eta.gov.lk),Cost of Lunch &amp; Dinner throughout the tour,Expenses of personal nature,Any other service not specified above.Entrance fees &amp; joining fees for adventure tours and safari tours,Sightseeing places not included in the Tour Agenda,Meal costs other than included in the Hotel bookings,Driver tips,Transport -A/C CAR – USD 65 Per day', '', '&nbsp;31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '&nbsp;31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '2017-03-22', '2017-12-20', NULL, '2013-05-05thushanc34afb4db60bc9c.jpg-1490179953.jpg', '29SRILANKA-videoSixteenByNine3000.jpg-1490179953.jpg,,', 4, 56000, '2017-03-22 17:52:33', '2017-03-25 14:49:09'),
