am freely &nbsp;during the day and a herd structure allowed form.(Entrance fee – USD 35 per/USD 23 per child).<br>&nbsp;The city of Kandy, which lies in the centre of Sri Lanka at an elevation of about 485 meters above sea &nbsp; level.<br>&nbsp;The Ulpange or the Queen’s bathing Pavilion - Situated partly in the waters of the Kandy Lake and &nbsp; &nbsp;the other part on land near the Temple &nbsp; &nbsp; of the &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tooth Relic.<br>&nbsp; Kandy Lake - This artificial lake was built by the last king of Kandy.<br>&nbsp; Visit the Kandy Museum and the Market Place.<br>&nbsp; Meals &nbsp;: Bed and Breakfast basis.&nbsp;<br><b><br></b><b style="color: inherit;">DAY 02- KANDY– BENTOTA</b><span style="color: inherit; font-weight: 700;">:</span><br>&nbsp;After breakfast proceed to Waskaduwa (Approximately 04 hours).<br>&nbsp;Madu River - The bio-diversity of the Madu River is of monumental signification when considering the &nbsp;wide ranges of aquatic and avian life &nbsp;as well as &nbsp;wetland dwelling amphibians, reptiles, mammals that &nbsp;inhabit the environs of this natural treasure. Bird watchers will be pleased &nbsp;to know that 111 &nbsp;species of &nbsp;bird have been identified in the mangrove formed environs of the river, and has been known to host &nbsp;several &nbsp;types of migratory birds.<br>&nbsp;Take a boat ride at the river (Per Boat – TK. 2200).<br>&nbsp;Kosgoda Sea Turtle - Conservation Project operated by the Wild Life Protection Society of SriLanka, &nbsp;It was established in 1988 to protect &nbsp;Sri Lanka’s &nbsp;turtles from extinction (Per adult/child – TK. 900).<br>&nbsp; Meals : Bed and Breakfast.<br><b><br></b><b style="color: inherit;">DAY 03- BENTOTA&nbsp;</b><br>&nbsp; Breakfast at the hotel.<br>&nbsp; At leisure.<br>&nbsp; Meals : Bed and Breakfast.<br><b><br></b><b style="color: inherit;">DAY 04 - WADDUWA - AIRPORT</b><br>&nbsp;After breakfast relax at the hotel.<br>&nbsp;Later proceed to airport for departure flight (Approximately 02 hours) - Please be at the airport 05 &nbsp;hours prior to flight departure.</font><br></h3>', '&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nAll\r\nHighway Toll fees,\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nHotel\r\nAccommodation at the above mentioned hotels on 01 DBL Room – BB basis, \r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nHotels\r\ncheck in by 12:00 hrs. Check out by at 12:00 noon unless otherwise arranged,\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nHotels\r\nwill be confirmed on availability at the time of booking. Alternatives will be\r\nsuggested (if unavailable) prior to confirmation.', '&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nAirfare\r\nand Visa fee.(Online Visa application can be done at www.eta.gov.lk)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nCost\r\nof Lunch &amp; Dinner throughout the tour.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nExpenses\r\nof personal nature.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nAny\r\nother service not specified above.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nEntrance\r\nfees &amp; joining fees for adventure tours and safari tours.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nSightseeing\r\nplaces not included in the Tour Agenda.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nMeal\r\ncosts other than included in the Hotel bookings.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nDriver\r\ntips.\r\n\r\nTransport -A/C CAR – USD 65\r\nPer day', '', '', '', '2017-05-01', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'Elephant orphanage.jpg-1490436001.jpg', 'Bentota_Srilanka.jpg-1490436001.jpg,Kosdoga_srilanka1.jpg-1490436001.jpg,Kandy Lake2.jpg-1490436001.jpg', 3, 50000, '2017-03-25 17:00:01', '2017-04-04 13:51:21');
