(116, 1, 0, 0, 'BALI & THE GILI ISLAND', 'INDONESIA', 'BALI', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '6 DAYS / 5 NIGHTS', NULL, '<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15.0396px;">Bali is an Indonesian island known for its forested volcanic mountains, iconic rice paddies, beaches and coral reefs. The island is home to religious sites such as cliffside Uluwatu Temple. To the south, the beachside city of Kuta has lively bars, while Seminyak, Sanur and Nusa Dua are popular resort towns. The island is also known for its yoga and meditation retreats.</span><br>', '<div><b>Day 01:</b>&nbsp;</div><div>Welcome To Lombok – Sasak Tour – Hotel<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span> (L)</div><div>Upon arrival to the airport, meeting&nbsp; with the guide, then the tour operator will take you to visit</div><div>Tanjung A’an at Kuta beach – one of the most scenic and un-spoilt beaches in this</div><div>part of the island. Lunch is served at one of the local restaurant at Kuta area. Sade</div><div>village – featuring the unique traditional lodge with its buffalo dung floors,</div><div>Sukarare village; renowned for its traditional hand weaving of brightly patterned</div><div>songket, ikat and sarong cloth, after that Banyumulek, famous for its traditional</div><div>pottery – check in hotel.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Day 02:</b></div><div> Fullday Gili Trawangan Tour (B/L)</div><div>After breakfast at hotel, start the tour to visit Lendang Bajur morning market is the</div><div>first place to visit before the trip is carried on to Pusuk pass; a green tropical rain</div><div>forest offering beautiful panorama of the green hill and valley, here, wild monkeys</div><div>await you for peanuts and bananas. Then a short transfer by outrigger boat will</div><div>take you to Gili islands for snorkeling and swimming, where, you can enjoy the</div><div>colorful coral reefs and varieties of tropical fish. On the way back to your hotel, you</div><div>may stop by at Malimbu hill for picture taking.(snorkeling equipment in optional).</div><div>Back to hotel.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Day 03:</b></div><div>&nbsp;Depart Lombok – Airport/ Flight To Denpasar – Hotel (B)</div><div>After breakfast at the hotel the transfer directly to Airport Lombok to fly to Bali.</div><div>Upon arrival in Bali, will meet and greet by our guide then direct transfer to hotel</div><div>for check in and overnight.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Day 04:</b> Fullday Bedugul – Megawi – Alas Kedaton – Tanah Lot Tour (B/D)</div><div>Inhale the crisp mountain air at the cool resort of Bedugul. Along the way, visit the</div><div>traditional markets in Candi Kuning, Marvel at the calm blue waters of Lake</div><div>Beratan. Afterwards, visit the monkey forest at Alas Kedaton before we proceed to</div><div>the famous seaside temple of Tanah Lot where we can see one of the most</div><div>spectacular sunset settings in the word. Program ended by Seafood Dinner at</div><div>Jimbaran Beach.Return back to hotel.</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Day 05:</b> Free Program On Your Own (<b>B)</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Day 06 :</b>Departure Bali – Airport &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <b>&nbsp;(B)</b></div>', '&nbsp;Return Air Ticket by (Dhaka-Bali) with all taxes ,Private transport AC with English speaking guide, Accommodation for 02 nights in Lombok &amp; 03 nights in Bali, lowest category room, &nbsp;Meals: Daily breakfast at hotel, 2x Lunch at Local Restaurant &amp; 1x Dinner at Local Restaurant, &nbsp;Entrance fee, Toll &amp; Parking fees as per program, &nbsp;Refreshment', '', '', '', '', '2017-03-25', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'Gili-Islands.jpg-1490457310.jpg', 'santosa-villas.jpg-1490457310.jpg,snorkelling.jpg-1490457310.jpg,Water Crossing.jpg-1490457310.jpg', 4, 59999, '2017-03-25 10:55:10', '2017-04-05 18:25:14');
