(126, 1, 0, 0, 'SCENIC BEAUTY LADAKH [BG-IND-STIC 00006]', 'INDIA', 'Leh | Monasteries | Uletokpo | Lamayuru | Khardongla | Nubra | Pangong Lake', 'TSL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '9 Days  8 Nights', NULL, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-family: " century="" gothic",="" sans-serif;="" color:="" black;="" background-image:="" initial;="" background-position:="" background-size:="" background-repeat:="" background-attachment:="" background-origin:="" background-clip:="" initial;"="">The Ladakh region is\r\nnestled in between the Himalayas and the Karakoram mountain ranges. It is\r\nuntouched by the hustle and bustle of people and does not boast of a torrid\r\ncity life. In its serene demeanour, it impresses with its beauty studded with\r\nlakes, snow-capped mountains, green patches of land, bright blue skies and\r\nunimaginable terrains. If Kashmir is the Paradise on Earth then Ladakh is no\r\nless in terms of sheer scenic beauty. Nubra valley, the lakes- Tsokar,\r\nTsomoriri and Pangong of the Ladakh region are the most beautiful parts of\r\nLadakh.</span><o:p></o:p></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;\r\nbackground:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black">Route plan&nbsp;</span></b><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\r\nABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black">Itinerary<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;\r\nbackground:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black">One day kolkata for free eye check up with hotel\r\nfacilities,<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;\r\nbackground:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black">Route plan: Dhaka- Kolkata (1 night stop over) –Delhi-Leh-same\r\nreturn route<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;\r\nbackground:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;\r\nbackground:white"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:black">Day 1:&nbsp;<span style="mso-bidi-font-weight:bold">Kolkata</span><o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;\r\nbackground:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black">Free eye check up with free appointed\r\nhospital/doctor @ Kolkata or enjoy free time.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day 2: Kolkata-Delhi-Leh</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#333333"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:black">Take morning flight to New Delhi &amp; connecting flight to leh\r\nairport.&nbsp;On arrival at Leh airport, you will be met by our representative\r\nat the airport and escort you to Hotel (Royal Ladakh***/equivalent)</span><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">. Complete day for the acclimatization which is 3500 Mtrs above\r\nsea level. Evening short walk around Leh bazaar Overnight at Hotel.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day 3: Monasteries</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#333333"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day excursion to the famous monasteries, it is interesting to\r\nvisit early in the morning to enjoy the praying ceremony at Thiksey monastery.\r\nContinue drive to Hemis monastery which is one of the most famous monasteries\r\nof the Ladakh region. On the way back visit to Shey Palace. Overnight at Hotel.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day 4: Alchi- Uletokpo</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#333333"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Leave for Uletokpo camping which is one of the most beautiful\r\ncamping in the Ladakh region on the way visit Spituk monastery which is just 5\r\nkms from Leh town. Continue drive to Alchi monastery is the only monastery in\r\nthe Ladakh on flat ground. By the lunch time you will reach Uletokpo. Overnight\r\nat Camp.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day 5: Uletokpo-Lamayuru</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#333333"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Leave Uletokpo and continue drive to Lamayuru via Khaltsi. From\r\nhere another 22 Kms drive will take you to Lamayuru. The oldest and\r\nspectacularly set Lamayuru monastery founded in the 10th Century. Visit the\r\nmonastery. In the late afternoon drive back to Leh which will take about 4/5\r\nhours drive. Overnight at Hotel.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day 6: Khardongla-Nubra</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#333333"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">After early breakfast at the hotel departure to Nubra Valley\r\nwith box lunch enroute visit Khardongla pass, Disket and Hundar monastery. On\r\narrival check in at&nbsp; Camp. Accommodation in tents.Dinner and overnight at\r\nthe camp.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day 7: Nubra-Leh</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#333333"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">After breakfast at the camp, Departure to Leh with lunch box.On\r\narrival check in at the hotel.Rest of the day free for shopping and independent\r\nactivities.Dinner and overnight at the hotel.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day 8: Pangong Lake- Leh</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#333333"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Leave early morning at 5AM to Pangong Lake through Changla pass\r\n5486 Mtrs. While ascending Changla pass 5486 Mtrs. Enjoy the beautiful\r\npanoramic view of the villages below the pass. Enjoy the landscape in the back\r\ndrop of the Lake. This famous blue brackish Lake of Pangong is 5/6 Kms wide and\r\nover 144 Kms long with half of it’s running the other side of the “INDO CHINA\r\nBORDER”. One rarely feels so close to nature and environment and the scenery is\r\nunforgettable. In the late afternoon drive back to Leh. Overnight at Hotel.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:7.5pt;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#333333">Day 9: Leh-Delhi</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:ABeeZee;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#333333"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:TrackMoves/>\r\n  <w:TrackFormatting/>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning/>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:DoNotPromoteQF/>\r\n  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>\r\n  <w:LidThemeAsian>JA</w:LidThemeAsian>\r\n  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript>\r\n  <w:Compatibility>\r\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>\r\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>\r\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>\r\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>\r\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>\r\n   <w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark/>\r\n   <w:EnableOpenTypeKerning/>\r\n   <w:DontFlipMirrorIndents/>\r\n   <w:OverrideTableStyleHps/>\r\n   <w:UseFELayout/>\r\n  </w:Compatibility>\r\n  <m:mathPr>\r\n   <m:mathFont m:val="Cambria Math"/>\r\n   <m:brkBin m:val="before"/>\r\n   <m:brkBinSub m:val="&#45;-"/>\r\n   <m:smallFrac m:val="off"/>\r\n   <m:dispDef/>\r\n   <m:lMargin m:val="0"/>\r\n   <m:rMargin m:val="0"/>\r\n   <m:defJc m:val="centerGroup"/>\r\n   <m:wrapIndent m:val="1440"/>\r\n   <m:intLim m:val="subSup"/>\r\n   <m:naryLim m:val="undOvr"/>\r\n  </m:mathPr></w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:Late