(127, 1, 0, 0, 'GLIMPSE OF LEH', 'INDIA', 'Leh | Monasteries | Khardongla pass | Pangong Lake', 'TSL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '5 nights 6 Days', NULL, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0in;text-align:justify;line-height:150%"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: " century="" gothic",="" sans-serif;="" background-image:="" initial;="" background-position:="" background-size:="" background-repeat:="" background-attachment:="" background-origin:="" background-clip:="" initial;"="">Few places in<span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif""=""><a href="http://lonelyplanet.com/india" title="India" style="word-wrap: break-word; outline: none; cursor: pointer; text-align: start;"><span style="color: windowtext; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">India</span></a></span><span class="apple-converted-space"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: " century="" gothic",="" sans-serif;="" background-image:="" initial;="" background-position:="" background-size:="" background-repeat:="" background-attachment:="" background-origin:="" background-clip:="" initial;"=""><span style="text-align: start;">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: " century="" gothic",="" sans-serif;="" background-image:="" initial;="" background-position:="" background-size:="" background-repeat:="" background-attachment:="" background-origin:="" background-clip:="" initial;"="">are at once so traveller-friendly and yet so enchanting and\r\nhassle-free as mountain-framed Leh. Dotted with stupas and crumbling mudbrick\r\nhouses, the Old Town is dominated by a dagger of steep rocky ridge topped by an\r\nimposing Tibetan-style palace and fort. Beneath, the bustling bazaar area is\r\ndraped in a thick veneer of tour agencies, souvenir shops and tandoori-pizza\r\nrestaurants, but a web of lanes quickly fans out into a green suburban\r\npatchwork of irrigated barley fields. Here, gushing streams and narrow\r\nfootpaths link traditionally styled Ladakhi homes and hotels that feature flat\r\nroofs, sturdy walls and ornate wooden window frames. Leh’s a place that’s all too\r\neasy to fall in love with – but take things very easy on arrival as the\r\naltitude requires a few days'' acclimatization before you can safely start\r\nenjoying the area''s gamut of adventure activities.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;\r\nmargin-bottom:6.0pt;margin-left:0in;text-align:right;line-height:150%" align="right"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: " century="" gothic",="" sans-serif;="" background-image:="" initial;="" background-position:="" background-size:="" background-repeat:="" background-attachment:="" background-origin:="" background-clip:="" initial;"="">Source: Lonely planet</span><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif""=""><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px;"><b>Route plan&nbsp;</b></span><span style="text-indent: 35.45pt;"><b><font size="2">Itinerary</font></b></span><br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px;">One day Kolkata for free eye check up with hotel facilities,</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px;">Route plan: Dhaka- Kolkata (1 night stop over) -Delhi- Leh- same return route,</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px;"><b>Day 1: Kolkata</b></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px;">Free eye check up with free appointed hospital/doctor @ Kolkata or enjoy free time.</span><br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><font size="2">Day 2: Kolkata - Delhi-Leh</font></b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Take morning flight to New Delhi &amp; connecting flight to leh airport.&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 10pt;">On arrival at Leh airport, you will be met by\r\nour representative at the airport and escort you to Hotel (</span><span style="font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;">Royal\r\nLadakh***/</span><font face="Calibri, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14.6667px;">equivalent</span></font><span style="font-size: 10pt;">) Complete day for the </span><span style="font-size: 13.3333px;">acclimatisation</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;which is 3500 meters above sea level. In the evening enjoy short walk\r\naround Leh bazaar along with Overnight stay at Hotel.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif""="">Day 3: Monasteries<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n" century="" gothic","sans-serif""="">Day excursion to the famous monasteries, it is\r\ninteresting to visit early in the morning to enjoy the praying ceremony at\r\nThiksey monastery. Continue drive to Hemis monastery which is one of the most\r\nfamous monasteries of the Ladakh region. On the way back visit to Shey Palace.\r\nOvernight stay at Hotel.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif""="">Day 4: Khardongla pass<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n" century="" gothic","sans-serif""="">After breakfast full day excursion to Khardongla\r\npass which is the highest motorable pass in the world 5600 Mtrs and has been\r\nrecorded in the Guinness Book of world records. At the top enjoy the nature\r\nbeauty of snow capped mountain. In the evening return back to the hotel. Overnight stay at\r\nHotel.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif""="">Day 5: Pangong Lake<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n" century="" gothic","sans-serif""="">Leave early morning at 5AM to Pangong Lake\r\nthrough Changla pass 5486 Mtrs. While ascending Changla pass 5486 Mtrs, enjoy\r\nthe beautiful panoramic view of the villages below the pass. After crossing the\r\npass halt for picnic lunch at Tsoltak, the summer pastureland of the yaks.\r\nArrive Durbuk and from there a short drive takes you to the western shore of\r\nthe lake. Enjoy the landscape in the back drop of the Lake. This famous blue\r\nbrackish Lake of Pangong is 5/6 Kms wide and over 144 Kms long with half of\r\nit’s running the other side of the “INDO CHINA BORDER”. One rarely feels so\r\nclose to nature and environment and the scenery is unforgettable. In the late\r\nafternoon drive back to Leh. Overnight stay at Hotel.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 115%;" century="" gothic","sans-serif""=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Day 6: Leh - Delhi-Kolkata-Dhaka&nbsp;</span></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 115%;" century="" gothic","sans-serif""=""><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Cross check to </span><span style="font-size: 13.3333px;">availability</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;of all the flights on time.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n" century="" gothic","sans-serif""="">Transfer in time to the airport for\r\nonwards destination flight.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><br></p>', 'Air\r\nFare round trip (Dhaka-Kolkata-Delhi-Leh-Dhaka),Accommodation\r\nin proposed hotels or similar,Transfers\r\nand sightseeing non AC private car/ van,Breakfast\r\n&amp; dinner in all places,Assistance\r\non arrival/ departure,Entrance\r\nfee &amp; inner line permit,All\r\ncurrently applicable taxes', 'Lunch,Guide\r\nduring sightseeing,Any\r\njoy ride,Personal\r\nexpense Tips, Travel Insurance &amp; Laundry,Any\r\ntable drinks (Alcoholic/ Mineral/Aerated)', '', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,\r\n\r\n30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,\r\n\r\n20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,\r\n\r\n30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,\r\n\r\n20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '2017-05-01', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'Leh_3.jpg-1490520594.jpg', 'Leh_6.jpg-1490520594.jpg,Khardunga_1.jpg-1490520594.jpg,Leh_2.jpg-1490520594.jpg', 3, 78999, '2017-03-26 16:29:54', '2017-03-29 17:17:50'),
