ialist doctor consultation at AMRI Hospital.At evening, free and easy time,<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-weight: 700;"><span segoe="" ui="" light","sans-serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:"segoe="" light""="" style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 15.3333px;">Day 04:</span></span><span segoe="" ui="" light","sans-serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:"segoe="" light""="" style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 15.3333px;">&nbsp;After Breakfast spend free and easy time. Check out of the hotel and Return to Dhaka. &nbsp;</span></p>', '<br>', 'Package includes:Return airfare: Dhaka-Kolkata-Dhaka, Accommodation: 3* Hotel standard (Golden apple boutique hotel),Well women checkup: AMRI Hospital,&nbsp;Complimentary Breakfast,Complimentary usage of Rest &amp; Fly lounge at HSIA.', '·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nAny\r\nother cost that are not mentioned above.', 'Full\r\ncardiac checkup includes: Complete\r\nHaemogram| Glucose | Uric acid | Urine Routine | Uric Acid | Urine Routine |\r\nStool Routine | TSH | PSA / PAP Smear | ECG | Mammography / Sonomamo | X-ray\r\nChest PA View |&nbsp; USG Pelvis (Screening) |\r\nDietician Consultation | TSH.', 'Upon\r\nadvance payment only', 'Medical packages once sold and confirmed is not refundable or exchangeable with other offers,Medical packages once sold and confirmed cannot be Transferable to other passengers.', '2017-03-26', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'Screenshot_4.png-1490607137.png-1490675627.png', 'Screenshot_7.png-1490607137.png-1490675627.png,Screenshot_5.png-1490607137.png-1490675627.png,Screenshot_9.png-1490607137.png-1490675627.png', 3, 20499, '2017-03-26 17:33:18', '2017-04-05 08:37:48'),
(131, 1, 0, 0, 'JUNGLE WALK @ TAMAN NEGARA [Product Code-AFM00002-M]', 'MALAYSIA', 'KUALA TAHAN', 'TSL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '3 Days 2 Nights', NULL, '<div style="text-align: justify;">Taman Negara was established at the Titiwangsa Mountains, Malaysia, in 1938/1939 as the King George V National Park. It was renamed to Taman Negara after independence, which means "national park" in Malay. Taman Negara has a total area of 4,343 km2 and has a reputation as the world''s oldest deciduous rainforest, estimated to be more than 130 million years old. Despite the reputation, the title of "oldest tropical rainforest" more accurately belongs to the Daintree Rainforest in Queensland, Australia, estimated to be between 135 million years old and 180 million years old.</div><div style="text-align: justify;"><br></div><div style="text-align: justify;">Taman Negara encompasses three states, Pahang, Kelantan and Terengganu, each with its own legislation. The Taman Negara Enactment (Pahang) No. 2 of 1939 is enforced in the state of Pahang, the Taman Negara Enactment (Kelantan) No. 14 of 1938 in the state of Kelantan and the Taman Negara Enactment (Terengganu) No. 6 of 1939 in the state of Terengganu. The enactments have similar contents.</div><div style="text-align: justify;"><br></div><div style="text-align: justify;">The park has been developed into a famous ecotourism destination in Malaysia. There are several geological and biological attractions in the park. Gunung Tahan is the highest point of the Malay Peninsula; climbers can use Kuala Tahan or Merapoh[5]as their departure point. Taman Negara is the home of some rare mammals, such as the Malayan tiger, crab-eating macaque, Malayan gaur (seladang) and Indian elephant. As well as birds such as the great argus, red junglefowl, and the rare Malayan peacock-pheasant are still found here in some numbers. Tahan River has been preserved to protect the Malaysian mahseer (ikan kelah in Malay), a type of game fish.</div><div style="text-align: justify;">Others attractions found near Kuala Tahan (Park headquarters for Pahang) include a canopy walkway, Gua Telinga (cave system), Lata Berkoh (rapid). Visitors can enjoy the tropical rainforest, birdwatching or jungle trekking (e.g. Tenor Rentis) and the river views along the Tahan River.</div>', '<div>DAY 01 – KUL / TAMAN NEGARA</div><div>You will be met in your hotel lobby in the city centre between 0730hrs to 0815hrs to be transferred to the coach departing point to embark on a 4 hours journey to Kuala Tembeling jetty. &nbsp;Board a motorised longboat for another 3 hours to Kuala Tahan, the headquarters of Taman Negara. &nbsp;On arrival at Kuala Tembeling, please proceed to register yourself with the National Park and Wildlife Department. &nbsp;The longboat departs at 1330 hours. &nbsp;En route you will be passing by local villages and lush tropical rainforest. &nbsp;Any sightings of birds, monkeys, monitor lizards or water buffaloes are a bonus. &nbsp;Sighting of wildlife cannot be guaranteed due to the dense and huge area of Taman Negara (4343 sq km). &nbsp;Expected arrival at Kuala Tahan is 1700 hours. &nbsp;Register at the reception of Taman Negara Resorts, dinner at Sri Mutiara Restaurant,at leisure till 2000hrs where your Nature guide will meet you for your night activity.</div><div><br></div><div>Your first adventure will be a night jungle walk in the 130 million years old tropical rainforest. &nbsp;We will be on a look-out for nocturnal insects amidst the chorus of the rainforest. &nbsp;Overnight in air-conditioned chalet.</div><div><br></div><div>DAY 02 – TAMAN NEGARA</div><div>Breakfast. &nbsp;We will start with a jungle walk up Teresik Hill. &nbsp;This walk takes us further into the national park. &nbsp;The guide will highlight to you the rich flora found en route. &nbsp;At the top of Teresik Hill, enjoy a panoramic view of the tropical rainforest and on a clear day, see &nbsp;Mount Tahan, the highest mountain in Peninsular Malaysia. &nbsp;Before returning to the base, we will go on a canopy walkway, built 40 metres above the ground and 450 meters in length. &nbsp;You will experience the rainforest from a different perspective, as you will be closer to the top of the trees!</div><div>Afternoon return to Resort, free at leisure,1900hrs Dinner at Sri Mutiara Restaurant , Overnight.</div><div><br></div><div>DAY 03 – TAMAN NEGARA/KUL</div><div>Breakfast. &nbsp;The boat for Kuala Tembeling departs at 0900hrs. &nbsp;This journey will take about 2 to 3 hours, depending on water level of the river. &nbsp;The transfer to Kuala Lumpur will depart by 1200 hours, expected arrival time at your hotel in Kuala Lumpur city centre is between 1530hrs to 1600hrs.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div>', 'Air\r\nFare round trip (DAC-KUL-DAC) ,\r\n\r\nAccommodation\r\nin proposed hotels,\r\n\r\nTransfers\r\nand sightseeing,\r\n\r\nBreakfast\r\n&amp; dinner in all places, \r\n\r\nAssistance\r\non arrival/ departure, \r\n\r\nEnglish speaking guide,\r\n\r\nEntrance\r\nfee &amp; inner line permit,', 'Personal\r\nexpense Tips, \r\n\r\nTravel\r\nInsurance &amp; Laundry,\r\n\r\nAny\r\ntable drinks (Alcoholic/ Mineral/Aerated)', 'Product code: AFM002', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,\r\n\r\n30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,\r\n\r\n20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '31 days or more before departure: 20% of the package cost,\r\n\r\n30 to 21 days before departure: 50% of the tour cost,\r\n\r\n20 days or less before departure: 100% of the package cost', '2017-05-01', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'Negara_8.jpg-1490587763.jpg', 'Negara_7.jpg-1490587763.jpg,Negara_9.jpg-1490587763.jpg,Negara_11.jpg-1490587763.jpg', 3, 50999, '2017-03-27 11:09:23', '2017-04-01 14:03:50'),
(132, 1, 0, 0, 'ROMANCE IN THAILAND', 'THAILAND', 'Phuket | Phi Phi Island | Krabi', 'TSL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '7 Days 6 Nights', NULL, '<p><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial;color:black"="">Thailand is an exotic, unique\r\nlandscape, complete with a culture unlike any other. Everything about it\r\nappeals to travellers, an aspect which has helped it to become one of the\r\nbiggest tourist destinations on the globe.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial;color:black"="">For those visiting for the first time,\r\nthere are numerous spots, dotted around the country, perfect for those wishing\r\nto get a starting taste of the exceptional culture on show. It''s unlikely\r\nyou''ll be able to visit all the tourist spots in this country in one go\r\nconsidering the size and shape of the country. However, the unadulterated\r\nbeauty of Thailand will certainly make your cheap holiday deals worthwhile. It\r\nis a &nbsp;<a href="http://falconholidays.ie/" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 204);">traveller’s\r\nparadise</span></a><span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>for those who\r\nwant to enjoy fantastic beaches and bewitching islands.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="">Krabi<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial;color:black"="">Krabi is a seaside town, the smallest\r\ndestination on this list, and features some stunning scenery representing the\r\nvery best of Thailand. The beaches attract divers and snorkelers and those\r\nwishing to visit the Phi Phi Islands can do so from here. The rainforests and\r\nlimestone cliffs are worth checking out as well and it''s certainly one of the\r\nmore peaceful locations about, though there are a range of water-sports\r\navailable for those seeking something a little more thrilling.</span><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:" arial","sans-serif";color:black"=""><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="">Phuket<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial;color:black"="">Phuket is the largest beach destination,\r\npopular with tourists, in all of Asia, lying serenely in the Andaman Sea.\r\nAgain, visitors are treated to golden sands, clear waters and five-star hotels,\r\nwith restaurants serving a large, delicious array of seafood every night and\r\nday. The Old Town features some culture as well and the<span class="apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a href="http://www.lonelyplanet.com/thailand/andaman-coast/phuket-town/sights/religious-sites/shrine-serene-light" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: " century="" gothic",="" sans-serif;="" color:="" rgb(0,="" 0,="" 204);"="">Shrine of the Serene Light</span></a><span class="apple-converted-space"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;color:black"="">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";mso-bidi-font-family:arial;="" color:black"="">is a special location, definitely worth a visit.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: " century="" gothic",="" sans-serif;="" color:="" black;="" background-image:="" initial;="" background-position:="" background-size:="" background-repeat:="" background-attachment:="" background-origin:="" background-clip:="" initial;"="">Return Air ticket\r\n(Dhaka-Bangkok-Dhaka) with all applicable taxes by US-Bangla Airlines, 6 nights\r\ncomfortable stay at&nbsp;3*standard Hotel in krabi,phi phi island &amp; Phuket.\r\nAccommodation is based on Twin sharing basis, Complimentary Breakfast, Free\r\nWi-Fi Internet.</span><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:" century="" gothic","sans-serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:arial;color:black"=""><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"></p><ul><li>2 nights at Holiday\r\nInn Resort Patong Phuket, Superior Room with ABF<br></li><li>2 nights at Holiday\r\nInn Resort Phi Phi Island, Garden Bungalow with ABF<br></li><li>2 nights at Holiday\r\nInn Resort Krabi, Premier Garden View Room with ABF<br></li><li>Phuket City tour\r\nwith Tiger Kingdom Entry (Big Tiger) on Private Car<br></li><li>Phuket Fantasea\r\nShow Dinner with SIC transfers<br></li><li>James Bond Island\r\nby Speed Boat with Canoeing, Elephant Trekking, ATV Ride, Fish Spa &amp; Thai\r\nLunch - SIC transfers<br></li><li>Phi Phi Island by\r\nBig Boat with snorkeling and Thai Lunch (Include National Marine Park Fee) with\r\nSIC Transfers and then Drop at Phi Phi Hotel by Private Long tail boat<br></li><li>Krabi Rainforest\r\nDiscovery Tour with Picnic Lunch with SIC transfers<br></li><li>Phuket Airport –\r\nPhuket Hotel and Krabi Hotel - Krabi Airport by Private SUV<br></li><li>Phi Phi Hotel-Krabi\r\nHotel by Joined Ferry<br></li></ul><p></p>', 'Return Air ticket (Dhaka-Bangkok-Dhaka) with all applicable taxes\r\nby Biman Bangladesh Airlines, 4 nights comfortable stay at&nbsp;3*standard Hotel in\r\nBangkok &amp;Pattaya, Accommodation is based on Twin sharing basis, Complimentary Breakfast, Free Wi-Fi Internet', 'Camera fee,Travel Insurance,Any offline airfare,Alcoholic/ Non-Alcoholic Beverages&nbsp;', '', '', '', '2017-05-01', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'krabi.jpg-1490610725.jpg', 'Phi Phi island1.jpg-1490610725.jpg,Phuket1.jpg-1490610725.jpg,Thailand34.jpg-1490610725.jpg', 3, 88000, '2017-03-27 17:32:05', '2017-03-29 10:18:48'),
