(134, 1, 0, 0, 'CHILLED BANGKOK', 'THAILAND', 'BANGKOK', 'TSL', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, '3 Days / 2 Nights', NULL, 'Bangkok, Thailand’s capital, is a large city known for ornate shrines and vibrant street life. The boat-filled Chao Phraya River feeds its network of canals, flowing past the Rattanakosin royal district, home to opulent Grand Palace and its sacred Wat Phra Kaew Temple. Nearby is Wat Pho Temple with an enormous reclining Buddha and, on the opposite shore, Wat Arun Temple with its steep steps and Khmer-style spire.<br>', '<br>', '&nbsp;Return Air ticket (Dhaka-Bangkok-Dhaka) , 2 nights comfortable stay at Grand President or Ambassadar at Bangkok&nbsp;Accommodation Twine share basis,Complimentary Breakfast', '', '', '', '', '2017-03-27', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'top10-nightlife-silom.jpg-1490630717.jpg', 'night-market-t.jpg-1490630717.jpg,Floating.jpg-1490630718.jpg,cover_large_p18sl6fp1p12651tiu1m901c9hfjr3.jpg-1490630718.jpg', 4, 29999, '2017-03-27 11:05:17', '2017-04-05 19:33:55'),
(135, 1, 0, 0, 'ELEPHANT ISLAND - KOH CHANG & BANGKOK', 'THAILAND', 'BANGKOK - KOH CHENG', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '5 Days / 4 Nights', NULL, '<div>Bangkok, Thailand’s capital, is a large city known for ornate shrines and vibrant street life. The boat-filled Chao Phraya River feeds its network of canals, flowing past the Rattanakosin royal district, home to opulent Grand Palace and its sacred Wat Phra Kaew Temple. Nearby is Wat Pho Temple with an enormous reclining Buddha and, on the opposite shore, Wat Arun Temple with its steep steps and Khmer-style spire. Ko Chang, one of the largest Thai islands in the Gulf of Thailand, contains dense, steep jungle. Mu Ko Chang National Park, a preserve with hiking trails and waterfalls such as tiered Klong Plu, covers the interior and extends to offshore coral reefs. The coast is dotted with beaches and villages including Bang Bao, built on piers. Hat Tha Nam (aka Lonely Beach) has a waterfront party scene that attracts backpackers.</div>', '<br>', '1.Return Air ticket (Dhaka-Bangkok) with all applicable taxes by Biman Bangladesh Airlines, 2.Two nights of hotel accommodation + daily breakfast (Bangkok) *** Based on 1st room category, 3.Two nights of hotel accommodation + daily breakfast (Koh Chang) *** Based on 1st room category, 4.Private Transfer (Suvarnabhumi Airport - Bangkok Hotel), 5.Private Transfer (Koh Chang Hotel - Suvarnabhumi Airport).', '', '', '', '', '2017-03-28', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'Koh-Chang2.jpg-1490675723.jpg', 'IMG_6144-Cover-620x413.jpg-1490675723.jpg,about-ko-chang-island.jpg-1490675723.jpg,6d4050093644233533bfc919fb986295.jpg-1490675723.jpg', 4, 37999, '2017-03-28 11:35:23', '2017-04-05 19:32:23'),
(136, 1, 0, 0, 'PEARL OF THE ANDAMAN - PHUKET ISLANDS & BANGKOK', 'THAILAND', 'BANGKOK - PHUKET', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '5 Days / 4 Nights', NULL, '<div>Phuket, a rainforested, mountainous island in the Andaman Sea, has some of Thailand’s most popular beaches, mostly situated along the clear waters of the western shore. The island is home to many high-end seaside resorts, spas and restaurants. Phuket City, the capital, has old shophouses and busy markets. Patong, the main resort town, has many nightclubs, bars and discos.<br></div><div>Bangkok, Thailand’s capital, is a large city known for ornate shrines and vibrant street life. The boat-filled Chao Phraya River feeds its network of canals, flowing past the Rattanakosin royal district, home to opulent Grand Palace and its sacred Wat Phra Kaew Temple. Nearby is Wat Pho Temple with an enormous reclining Buddha and, on the opposite shore, Wat Arun Temple with its steep steps and Khmer-style spire.</div><div><br></div>', '<br>', '1.Return Air ticket (Dhaka-Bangkok) with all applicable taxes by Biman Bangladesh Airlines,2.Two nights of hotel accommodation + daily breakfast (Bangkok) *** Based on 1st room category ***,3.Two nights of hotel accommodation + daily breakfast (Phuket) *** Based on 1st room category ***,4.Private Transfer (Suvarnabhumi Airport - Bangkok Hotel),5.SIC Transfer (Phuket Airport - Phuket Hotel) @ between 08:00 - 18:00 Hours only *** Min of 3 paxs travelling shall upgrade --&gt; Private Transfer @ free of charge', '', '', '', '', '2017-03-28', '2017-12-20', NULL, '6ccc13d42116a2faef974d20e86df77b.jpg-1490676751.jpg', 'Phuket-Trip-Beaches-of-Phuket1.jpg-1490676751.jpg,catch_beach_club_night_lr.jpg-1490676751.jpg,A-night-dining-on-the-beah-next-to-the-Indian-ocean-at-the-Kuramathi-Resort-Maldives.jpg-1490676751.jpg', 4, 33999, '2017-03-28 11:52:31', '2017-04-05 19:52:58'),
(137, 1, 1, 0, 'DOYEN OF BACKPACKER - KOH SAMET & BANGKOK', 'THAILAND', 'BANGKOK - KOH SAMET', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '5 Days / 4 Nights', NULL, '<div>Once the doyen of backpacker destinations, today Ko Samet shares its charms with a wider audience. The sandy shores, cosy coves and aquamarine waters attract ferry-loads of Bangkokians looking to party each weekend, while tour groups pack out many resorts. Fire-juggling shows and beach barbecues are nightly events on the northern beaches, but the southern parts of the island are far more secluded and sedate.Bangkok, Thailand’s capital, is a large city known for ornate shrines and vibrant street life. The boat-filled Chao Phraya River feeds its network of canals, flowing past the Rattanakosin royal district, home to opulent Grand Palace and its sacred Wat Phra Kaew Temple. Nearby is Wat Pho Temple with an enormous reclining Buddha and, on the opposite shore, Wat Arun Temple with its steep steps and Khmer-style spire.&nbsp;</div>', '<br>', 'Return Air ticket (Dhaka-Bangkok) with all applicable taxes, Two nights of 4* hotel accommodation + daily breakfast (Bangkok) *** Based on 1st room category***, Two nights of 4* hotel accommodation + daily breakfast (Koh Samet) *** Based on room category ***, Private Transfer (Suvarnabhumi Airport - Bangkok Hotel), SIC Transfer (Bangkok Hotel - Banphe Pier) @ 08:30 Hours *** Min of 5 paxs travelling together shall upgrade &nbsp;Private Transfer @ free of charge ***, SIC Round trip Ferry or Shuttle Boat (Seree Banphe Pier / Chok Krissada - Koh Samet - Seree Banphe Pier / Chok Krissada).', '', '', '', '', '2017-03-28', '2017-12-20', NULL, '1408121701276256366.jpg-1490679483.jpg', 'Aktiviteter-i-Thailand.jpg-1490679485.jpg,maxresdefault.jpg-1490679485.jpg,rayong-hotels-L.jpg-1490679485.jpg', 4, 36999, '2017-03-28 12:32:09', '2017-04-05 19:40:42'),
(138, 1, 0, 0, 'MIRROR OF HIMALAYA - KATHMANDO & POKHARA', 'NEPAL', 'KATHMANDO - POKHARA - NAGARKOT', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '6 DAYS / 5 NIGHTS', NULL, '<div>Kathmandu is the capital and largest urban agglomerate of Nepal. Kathmandu is the gateway to tourism in Nepal. It is also the nerve center of the country''s economy. The city of Kathmandu was named after Kasthamandap temple that stands in Durbar Square. In Sanskrit, Kastha means "wood" and Mandap means "covered shelter". This temple, also known as Maru Satal, was built in 1596 by King Laxmi Narsingh Malla. The two-storey structure is made entirely of wood, and uses no iron nails nor supports. According to legend, all the timber used to build this pagoda was obtained from a single tree. The colophons of ancient manuscripts, dated as late as the 20th century, refer to Kathmandu as Kasthamandap Mahanagar in Nepal Mandala. Mahanagar means "great city". The city is called "Kasthamandap" in a vow that Buddhist priests still recite to this day. Thus, Kathmandu is also known as Kasthamandap. During medieval times, the city was sometimes called Kantipur. This name is derived from two Sanskrit words - Kanti and pur. "Kanti" is one of the names of the Goddess Lakshmi, and "pur" means place. Among the indigenous Newar people, Kathmandu is known as Yen Desa , and Patan and Bhaktapur are known as Yala Desa &nbsp;and Khwopa Desa ."Yen" is the shorter form of Yambu , which originally referred to the northern half of Kathmandu.</div><div><div><br></div><div>Far from the earthquake epicenter, and almost unaffected by the disaster, Pokhara ticks all the right boxes, with spectacular scenery, adventure activities, and accommodation and food choices galore. Whether you’ve returned from a three-week trek or endured a bus trip from hell, Lakeside Pokhara is the perfect place to recharge your batteries.The scene is a chilled-out version of Thamel, stretching along the shore of a tranquil lake with bobbing paddle boats. From the lake, and possibly even from your hotel bed, you can enjoy a clear view of the snow-capped mountains, just twenty or so kilometres away. There’s much more to Pokhara than its laid-back charm. It also boasts a booming adventure sports industry; it is arguably the best paragliding venue on the globe and is surrounded by white-water rivers. There''s a fascinating museum dedicated to the world-famous Gurkha soldier. And last but not least, it’s the gateway to the world-famous treks in and around the Annapurna range and beyond</div></div><div><br></div>', '<div>Destination Covered:<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">		</span>Kathmandu, Pokhara &amp; Nagarkot</div><div>Outline Itinerary:</div><div>Day 01: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Arrival and hotel transfer. O/N at Kathmandu.&nbsp;</div><div>Day 02: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Kathmandu - Pokhara transfer. O/N at Pokhara.</div><div>Day 03: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Pokhara sightseeing tour. O/N at Pokhara.</div><div>Day 04: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Pokhara to Kathmandu transfer. O/N at Kathmandu.</div><div>Day 05: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>KTM s/s tour &amp; Nagarkot transfer. O/N at Nagarkot.</div><div>Day 06: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Nagarkot to Airport departure.</div><div>Details Itinerary:</div><div>Day 01: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Arrival and Hotel transfer. O/N at Kathmandu.</div><div>Arrival Tribhuvan International Airport. It will around half an hour for immigration processing. Meet &amp; Greet our representative those who will wait for our valued clients with the name on placard in outside the arrival terminal. Transfer to hotel. Check in hotel. Evening free time.</div><div>Overnight stay at Kathmandu.</div><div>Kathmandu is the capital and largest urban agglomerate of Nepal. Kathmandu is the gateway to tourism in Nepal. It is also the nerve center of the country''s economy. The city of Kathmandu was named after Kasthamandap temple that stands in Durbar Square. In Sanskrit, Kastha means "wood" and Mandap means "covered shelter". This temple, also known as Maru Satal, was built in 1596 by King Laxmi Narsingh Malla. The two-storey structure is made entirely of wood, and uses no iron nails nor supports. According to legend, all the timber used to build this pagoda was obtained from a single tree.</div><div>The colophons of ancient manuscripts, dated as late as the 20th century, refer to Kathmandu as Kasthamandap Mahanagar in Nepal Mandala. Mahanagar means "great city". The city is called "Kasthamandap" in a vow that Buddhist priests still recite to this day. Thus, Kathmandu is also known as Kasthamandap. During medieval times, the city was sometimes called Kantipur. This name is derived from two Sanskrit words - Kanti and pur. "Kanti" is one of the names of the Goddess Lakshmi, and "pur" means place.</div><div>Among the indigenous Newar people, Kathmandu is known as Yen Desa , and Patan and Bhaktapur are known as Yala Desa &nbsp;and Khwopa Desa ."Yen" is the shorter form of Yambu , which originally referred to the northern half of Kathmandu.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>Day 02 : <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Kathmandu to &nbsp;POKHARA transfer. O/N at POKHARA.</div><div>Breakfast at hotel at 6/6:30 am. And proceed towards Pokhara at 07:00 am after 6/7 hour drive will reach at PKR. Check in hotel. Evening free time.</div><div>Overnight stay at Pokhara.</div><div>Pokhara is the third largest city of Nepal with an area of 55.22 km2 and a population of 264,991 inhabitants, making one of the densely populated city. The city is located approximately 200 km west of the country''s capital, Kathmandu. It serves as the headquarters of Kaski District, Gandaki Zone and the Western Development Region. Pokhara is the most popular tourist destination in Nepal. Three out of the ten highest mountains in the world — Dhaulagiri, Annapurna I and Manaslu — are within 30 miles (linear distance) of the city, so that the northern skyline of the city offers a very close view of the Himalayas. Due to its proximity to the Annapurna mountain range, the city is also a base for trekkers undertaking the Annapurna Circuit through the ACAP region of the Annapurna ranges in the Himalayas. Pokhara is the largest tourist city in the country, home to great Himalayan trails.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>Day 03: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">		</span>POKHARA sightseeing tour. O/N at POKHARA.</div><div>Breakfast at hotel around 6/6:30 am. After breakfast start Half day Pokhara sightseeing tour at 8: 00 am to visit Davis falls, Gupteshower Cave &amp; Seti River George. &nbsp;Finish and return back to hotel at 11: 00 pm. Day free for your own activities.</div><div>Overnight stay at Pokhara.</div><div>Day 04: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">		</span>Pokhara to Kathmandu transfer. O/N at Kathmandu.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">								</span></div><div>Breakfast at hotel around 6/6:30 am. Return back to Kathmandu at 08:00 am after 6/7 hour drive will arrive at Kathmandu. Check in hotel. Evening free time for the rest.</div><div>Overnight stay at Kathmandu.</div><div>Day 05: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">		</span>KTM s/s tour &amp; Nagarkot transfer. O/N at Nagarkot.</div><div>Breakfast at hotel. And start Half day KTM sightseeing tour to visit Basantapur Durbar Square &amp; Swayambhunath finish and transfer to Nagarkot. After one and half hour drive from Kathmandu will arrive at Nagarkot. Check in hotel. Evening enjoying the scenic view of sunset in magnificent Himalayan range from top of the hotel.</div><div>Overnight stay at Nagarkot.</div><div>Nagarkot : Located approximately 7000 ft (2000 m) above sea level and 28 km from Kathmandu International Airport, Nagarkot is a world famous hills station commanding breathtaking views of the majestic Himalayas, rolling hills, deep valleys, lush pine forests in a quaint rural atmosphere.</div><div>Considered as the best viewpoint spot to enjoy the magnificent sunrise and sunset with spectacular Himalayan vistas, Nagarkot commands one of the broadest views of the snowcapped Himalayas in the Kathmandu valley (8 Himalayan ranges of Nepal out of 13 from here). The ranges include Annapurna range, Manaslu range, Ganesh himal range, Langtang range, Jugal range, Rolwaling range, Mahalangur range( Everest range) and Numbur range with splendid views of the Kathmandu valley and Shivapuri national park.</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Day 06: <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">		</span>Nagarkot to airport Departure.</div><div>Wake up early morning at 4:30 am and enjoy with sunrise view from top of the hotel. After breakfast transfer to airport to connect flight for the final departure.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>', '1. Return Air ticket (Dhaka-Kathmando-Dhaka),&nbsp;2. Airport - Hotel - Airpor transfer by private deluxe vehicle,3.One Half day KTM sightseeing tour by private deluxe vehicle,4. KTM - PKR - KTM transfer by private deluxe vehicle with lunch on the way,5.On Half day PKR sightseeing tour by private deluxe vehicle,6.KTM - NAG - KTM transfer by private deluxe vehicle,7. 02 Nights accommodation @ Kathmandu on BB plan , inclusive of all the applicable government,taxes and service charges , currently 24.3% (subject to change without any prior notice )8. 02 Nights accommodation @ Pokhara on BB plan, inclusive of all the applicable government,taxes and service charges , currently 24.3% (subject to change without any prior notice )9. 01 Nights accommodation @ Nagarkot on BB plan, inclusive of all the applicable government,taxes and service charges , currently 24.3% (subject to change without any prior notice )', '', '', '', '', '2017-03-28', '2017-01-20', NULL, 'pokhara (1).jpg-1490715437.jpg', 'Pokhara.jpg-1490715437.jpg,38282018.jpg-1490715437.jpg,Paragrading-in-Nepal.jpg-1490715437.jpg', 3, 36999, '2017-03-28 10:37:17', '2017-04-05 19:39:51'),
(139, 5, 0, 0, 'KINGDOM OF KATHMANDU', 'NEPAL', 'KATHMANDU', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '3 days / 2 Nights', NULL, 'Kathmandu is the capital and largest urban agglomerate of Nepal. Kathmandu is the gateway to tourism in Nepal. It is also the nerve center of the country''s economy. The city of Kathmandu was named after Kasthamandap temple that stands in Durbar Square. In Sanskrit, Kastha means "wood" and Mandap means "covered shelter". This temple, also known as Maru Satal, was built in 1596 by King Laxmi Narsingh Malla. The two-storey structure is made entirely of wood, and uses no iron nails nor supports. According to legend, all the timber used to build this pagoda was obtained from a single tree. The colophons of ancient manuscripts, dated as late as the 20th century, refer to Kathmandu as Kasthamandap Mahanagar in Nepal Mandala. Mahanagar means "great city". The city is called "Kasthamandap" in a vow that Buddhist priests still recite to this day. Thus, Kathmandu is also known as Kasthamandap. During medieval times, the city was sometimes called Kantipur. This name is derived from two Sanskrit words - Kanti and pur. "Kanti" is one of the names of the Goddess Lakshmi, and "pur" means place. Among the indigenous Newar people, Kathmandu is known as Yen Desa , and Patan and Bhaktapur are known as Yala Desa &nbsp;and Khwopa Desa ."Yen" is the shorter form of Yambu , which originally referred to the northern half of Kathmandu.<br>', '<br>', 'Return Air ticket ( Dhaka- Kathmando),Airport - Hotel - Airpor transfer by private deluxe vehicle,One Half day KTM sightseeing tour by private deluxe vehicle,02 Nights accommodation @ Kathmandu on BB plan , inclusive of all the applicable governmenttaxes and service charges , currently 24.3% (subject to change without any prior notice ),', '', '', '', '', '2017-03-28', '2017-12-20', NULL, '27367Kathmandu-temple-N_2427964b.jpg-1490717007.jpg', 'kathmandu_tour.jpg-1490717007.jpg,kathmandu-valley-rim-circuit-trek.jpg-1490717007.jpg,hotel-vaishali.jpg-1490717007.jpg', 2, 20999, '2017-03-28 11:03:27', '2017-04-05 19:38:05'),
(140, 1, 0, 0, 'INTO THE SUNLIGHT - MYANMAR', 'MYANMAR', 'MANDALAY → MINGUN → BAGAN → INLE LAKE  → YANGON', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '7 Days / 6 Nights', NULL, '<div><div><span style="color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: Ubuntu-R;">Myanmar (formerly Burma) is a Southeast Asian nation of more than 100 ethnic groups, bordering India, Bangladesh, China, Laos and Thailand. Yangon (formerly Rangoon), the country''s largest city, is home to bustling markets, numerous parks and lakes, and the towering, gilded Shwedagon Pagoda, which contains Buddhist relics and dates to the 6th century.</span><br></div></div><span style="color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: Ubuntu-R;">Travelling is a part of this cheerful world, let travel whenever you can and still. As you make up your mind to go, please contact us for a wide choice of tours, and the best services at good price. We would like to offer you a tour to Myanmar, travelling around its symbolic sites, from temples and pagodas complex to its rustic sights of villages and nature. It will be fun</span><br><div><br></div>', '<div>Day 1 Mandalay Arrival</div><div>Meals:N/A</div><div>Activities:Land in Mandalay, check-in, visit Amarapura, Mahagandayon Monastery, Hand-Woven silk workshop, sunset at U-Pein wooden bridge</div><div>Upon arrival, a warm welcome from our guide at the airport. Transfer to Amarapura to visit Mahagandayon Monastery, housing over thousand of monks; visit the Myanmar traditional Hand-Woven silk workshop and stroll on the U Bein bridge built over centuries ago, the longest wooden bridge in Asia to enjoy the sunset over the bridge.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Evening return and overnight in Mandalay.</div><div><br></div><div>Day 2 Mandalay - Mingun - Mandalay&nbsp;</div><div>Meals:Breakfast</div><div>Activities:Boat to Mingun, visit Settawya Pagoda, Mingun Pahtotawgyi, Mingun Bell and Myatheintan Pagoda; back to Mandalay, visit Mahamuni Pagoda, Kyauktawgyi Pagoda, Shwenandaw (Golden Palace) monastery, Kuthodaw Pagoda and Sulamani Pagoda</div><div>After breakfast at the hotel, transfer to jetty for a private boat trip on the Ayeyarwaddy river to Mingun - a village 11km up stream from Mandalay by the west bank of the river. Visit Settawya Pagoda, Mingun Pahtotawgyi, world-renowned for the ringing Mingun Bell and Myatheintan Pagoda.</div><div>Return to Mandalay by noon. Afternoon sightseeing includes Mahamuni Pagoda, Kyauktawgyi Pagoda - a large Buddha statue carved out of a single block of marble, Shwenandaw (Golden Palace) monastery for its exquisite wood carving; Kuthodaw Pagoda where the world''s biggest book, the full Buddhist scriptures were carved in stone plaques individually placed in tomb-like structures, and finally visit Sulamani Pagoda.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Overnight in Mandalay.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Day 3 Mandalay - Bagan&nbsp;</div><div>Meals:Breakfast</div><div>Activities:Present in Bagan, visit a series of Nyaung U market, Shwezigon Pagoda, Htilominlo Temple, Gubyaukgyi Temple, drop by Myinkaba village, turn to Ananda Temple, Thabinnyu Temple and Dhammayangyi Temple, reach to Shwesandaw Pagoda and enjoy the sunset</div><div>After breakfast at the hotel, take morning flight to Bagan. On arrival Bagan; visit the colorful Nyaung U Market; Shwezigon Pagoda and its magnificent golden stupa; Htilominlo Temple masterfully decorated with carvings from sandstone and plaster; Gubyaukgyi Temple, with superb mural of Jataka tales; Myinkaba village to experience one of Myanmar''s best-known handicrafts, traditional lacquer-ware; Ananda Temple, an architectural masterpiece of the early century temple style with four impressive standing Buddha statues; Thabinnyu Temple, the highest temple in Bagan; Dhammayangyi Temple for its remarkable brickwork. Wind down with the sun setting over the far horizon, from the upper terrace of Shwesandaw Pagoda. Overnight in Bagan</div><div><br></div><div>Day 4 Bagan fly to Heho - Inle Lake</div><div>Meals:Breakfast</div><div>Activities:Fly to Heho, check-in, cruise along Inle Lake for sight-seeing, visit Phaung Daw Oo pagoda, Inpawkhon village and a local market</div><div>After breakfast at the hotel, take morning flight to Heho. On arrival, transfer to Nyaung Shwe jetty with boat transfer to hotel. Check-in to the hotel and commence sightseeing around Inle Lake by boat. Witness the famous single-leg canoe rowing; traditional fishing way; floating gardens; simple village life and breath-taking scenery. Also visit PhaungDawOo Pagoda, one of the main principle shrines in Myanmar, dating back to the 18th century; the lotus weaving village of Inpawkhon; a local market in the region (if open).&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Overnight in Inle Lake.</div><div><br></div><div>Day 5 Inle Lake (Inn Dein)</div><div>Meals:Breakfast</div><div>Activities:Visit a local market, trip to Shwe Inn Thein, head to Inn Dein Pagoda, drop by black smith workshop, Shan Cheroot making</div><div>After breakfast at the hotel, visit a local market in (if open). Boat trip to Shwe Inn Thein situated on west shore of Inle Lake, with a stair path leading to the mysterious Inn Dein Pagoda; Blacksmith workshop;Shan Cheroot (tobacco) making. Free afternoon at hotel and overnight in Inle Lake.</div><div><br></div><div>Day 6 Heho - Yangon&nbsp;</div><div>Meals:Breakfast</div><div>Activities:Fly to Yangon, explore the city including visiting Chaukhtatgyi Pagoda, Karaweik Hall Royal barge, Sule pagoda, Chinatown, Shwedagon Pagoda, colonial buildings and streets, enjoy the sunset</div><div>After breakfast at the hotel, take morning flight to Yangon. City tour starts by visiting Chaukhtatgyi Pagoda, a colossal reclining Buddha; Karaweik Hall Royal barge on the royal KanDawGyi lake with photo opportunity; Yangon city center featuring Sule Pagoda, streets of colonial buildings, downtown Chinatown with its distinct streets fruit market and other main boulevards of Yangon downtown. Tour ends at the world heritage site Shwedagon Pagoda, watch the golden dome spectacularly lit up by the magical sunset.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Overnight in Yangon.</div><div><br></div><div>Day 7 Yangon Shopping and Departure</div><div>Meals:Breakfast</div><div>Activities:Visit Bogyoke Market if possible, departure</div><div>After breakfast and check-out of the hotel, visit Bogyoke (Scott) Market (Close on Monday &amp; Public Holidays) filled with arts and handicrafts, fashion and jewelry. Airport transfers and concludes tour.</div><div><br></div>', 'Breakfasts,Lunch,Dinner,TransportCar,CruiseIncluded servicesReturn Air ticket(Dhaka-Yangoon)Hotel accommodation with daily breakfast,Double/Twin sharing basic,Domestic flight ticket with airport tax,Transportation - Internal transfers and sightseeing as per itinerary with private a/c car,Private boat arrangement at Mingun village-Mandalay and Boat ride at Inle Lake,Entrance fees as in itinerary,Purified drinking water &amp; cold towel on trip English speaking station guide service', 'ExclusionsMeals (Lunch/Dinner),&nbsp;Beverages,&nbsp;Drinks Trip insurance Airport departure tax at Yangon airport at USD10 per person,&nbsp;Visa Fees Tips and personal expenditure Any other services which are not listed in above prices include,Personal expense such as camera and Video fees, etc…. Bank handling fees,Early check in and late check out hotel,', '', '', '', '2017-03-29', '2017-12-20', NULL, 'vv.jpg-1491122983.jpg', 'THE LANDMARK SHWEDAGON-Mandalay mountain and kyone gyi.jpg-1491122428.jpg,bagan-sunrise-3883-edit.jpg-1490765387.jpg,THE LANDMARK SHWEDAGON-Inle indein pagoda 2.jpg-1491122428.jpg', 4, 129999, '2017-03-29 12:29:47', '2017-04-05 19:42:15');
