(142, 1, 0, 0, 'BORNEO Tours [BG-KUL- PAN 00005]', 'Malaysia', 'Kuala Lumpur | Kuching | Baku National Park | Damai Beach', 'TSL', 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, '10 Days 9 Nights', NULL, '<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 15.0396px;" class="cye-lm-tag">Imagine a city, with a skyline punctuated by minarets, Mogul-style domes and skyscrapers; imagine colourful, food-stall-lined streets shaded by a leafy canopy of banyan trees. Street Feast It won''t take you long to realise that, despite the heat, this is a city best explored on foot. Walk and you can catch all the action and save yourself the frustration of becoming entangled in one of KL''s all-too-frequent traffic jams. What''s more, you''ll be sure to come across some of the city''s best dining spots: the hawker stalls and traditional neighborhood kopitiam (coffee shops) that beckon you over with the aroma of freshly cooked food. Despite the city''s relentless march towards modernity, parts of KL retain the laid-back ambience and jungle lushness of the kampung (village) it once was. Historical Canvas Today''s KL-ites are separated by barely a handful of generations from the tenacious Chinese and Malay tin prospectors who founded the city, carving it out of virgin jungle. By the time the British made it the capital of Peninsular Malaysia in the late 19th century, erecting grand colonial buildings, KL had only been in existence for a couple of decades. Since then, the city has been the scene of history-defining moments for Malaysia. Stadium Merdeka was where, in 1957, the country’s first prime minister, Tunku Abdul Rahman, punched his fist seven times in the air and declared independence. Multicultural Modernity This is Kuala Lumpur (KL), Malaysia’s sultry capital packed with historic monuments, steel-clad skyscrapers, lush parks, megasized shopping malls, bustling street markets and lively nightspots. Essential parts of the vibrant mix are the incense-wreathed, colourfully adorned mosques and temples of the country’s Malay, Chinese and Indian communities. A reverence for these ancient cultures is balanced with a drive to be plugged into the contemporary world, a desire that''s reflected in an exciting contemporary-art and design scene, an ambitious riverbank-regeneration project and cutting-edge architecture: once completed, the new Merdeka PNB 118 tower will be taller than the iconic Petronas Towers.source: lonely planet</span><br>', '<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Day01&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Arrival\r\n– Putrajaya – Kuala Lumpur&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Upon arrival visit\r\nPutrajaya, the administrative centre of Malaysia built 25 km south of Kuala\r\nLumpur in the 1990’. The monumental buildings around the Putrajaya lake show an\r\nimpressive&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; combination of the\r\ntraditional and the modern architectural style.Overnight in Kuala Lumpur.</span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Day02&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kuala\r\nLumpur&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">After\r\nbreakfast&nbsp; half day city tour to discover\r\nthe beauty of an old and new Kuala Lumpur. Petronas Twin Towers, China Town,\r\nMasjid Jamek, old Royal King’s Palace, TheanHou temple, National Monument,\r\nNational Mosque, Railway Administrative building and Independence\r\nSquare.Overnight in Kuala Lumpur.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Day03&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kuala\r\nLumpur -Kuching</span></b><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag"> </span></b><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">After breakfast in\r\nhotel and free activity till the airport transfer for your flight to Kuching.\r\nUpon arrival in Kuching, meet and greet and transfer to your hotel</span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">. The rest of the day is on your own leisure. </span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">You\r\ncan have a walk at the charming Kuching Waterfront and have a look on the colourful\r\nshops selling typical local handcrafts. </span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Overnight in Kuching.</span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Day04&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kuching&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">After breakfast visit\r\nSarawak’s historic capital. Highlights\r\ninclude Kuching’s Chinatown, the Cat Statue (Kuching means “Cat” in\r\nMalay), the TuaPek Kong Chinese Temple the world famous Sarawak Museum and the\r\nCat Museum. Pass by the State Mosque and the Astana, the former residence of\r\nthe White Rajahs.&nbsp; Proceed on foot\r\nthrough Old Kuching, visit the colourful Central Market, pass by the&nbsp; White Rajah era, the Pavilion, the Square\r\nTower, the Court House, the Charles Brooke Monument and the Post Office.\r\nOvernight in Kuching.</span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Day05&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bako\r\nNational Park&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Full day excursion to\r\nthe small peninsula, 1,5 hours from Kuching by bus and longboat. Bako is home\r\nof the bizarre proboscis monkeys, the silver leaf langur monkeys, long-tailed\r\nmacaque monkeys, wild boar, flying squirrels and monitor lizards as well as\r\nhundreds of different bird species. You will discover the mangroves, strangling\r\nfigs, carnivorous pitcher plants and symbiotic ant plants. Packed lunch is\r\nincluded.Overnight in Kuching.</span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Day06&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kuching\r\n– Damai Beach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">After breakfast\r\ntransfer to Damai Beach for your beach holiday. Overnight at Damai Beach.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Day07-09 Damai Beach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Days free on your own leisure. Breakfasts\r\nin the hotel. </span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Overnight at Damai\r\nBeach.</span><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal cye-lm-tag" style="text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;"><b><span lang="EN-MY" class="cye-lm-tag">Day10 Damai Beach - Onwards&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 